x4freetext: Hg-196 isotopes the enriched sample was used.
For others isotopes the natural abundance sample
resolution 2.7 keV at E-gamma=1.332 MeV line of Co-60
Uranium cylindrical(d=10mm) target as source of
Beryllium placed in the center of graphite
cube with side 120 cm. Served as neutron moderator.
. Intensity of thermal neutrons was 4E+8 n/(s*cm2)
in the center of the graphite cube
for production of nuclei in high-spin and low-spin
states at the excitation energy equal to neutron
binding energy. High spin state is usually isomeric;
excepting Sr-85 and Sn-123 ( see formula (1) on page
where index l and h - for low and high spin states,
F(t) - time factor to allow for accumulation of nuclei
Ground-state nuclei result both directly from the
reaction and from the decay of the isomer.
Ratios were found for each observed gamma-line and
final IR was determined as their weighted mean.
